text:
Feb 12, 2017 at 11:58a ET 0Shares 
Kyle Busch is set to make his 12th start in the 59th annual Daytona 500 Feb. 26 at 2 p.m. ET on FOX. 
The 2015   champion has racked up wins at nearly every track, but the Great American Race has eluded him. 
Check out a collection of Busch's past Daytona 500 paint schemes and results: © , Michael L. Levitt © 2016, Michael L. Levitt 2005 
Busch’s first Daytona 500 didn’t go very well, finishing 38 th in his inaugural season driving the No. 5 Hendrick Motorsports Chevrolet. 
After a strong fourth-place qualifying effort, Busch could only manage a 23 rd -place finish. 2006 
After a strong fourth-place qualifying effort, Busch could only manage a 23 rd -place finish. no commercial use without express written consent-Copyright Robert LeSieur USA tel 843 672 9777or 704 534 7171-RobertLeSie Copyright Robert LeSieur 2007 
It was more of the same for Busch in 2007, qualifying eighth but only coming up with a 24 th -place result in his final Daytona 500 with Hendrick. NIgel Kinrade/Autostock 2008 
After making the switch to Joe Gibbs Racing, Busch earned his first top five in the Daytona 500, finishing fourth. Nigel Kinrade/Autostock 1240 Briers Creek Drive, Alpharetta, Georgia 30004 Nigel Kinrade 2009 
Busch started Speedweeks out strong, winning his qualifying race to start fourth, but after leading a race-high 88 laps, a crash in Turn 2 resulted in a 41 st -place finish. © Lesley Ann Miller 5405 Alton Pkwy Suite 5A-265 Irvine CA 92604 United States +1-949-892-3635 license@lesleyworld.com ©2009 Lesley Ann Miller 2010 
It was a mediocre showing for Busch in 2010, starting seventh and finishing 14 th in this No. 18 JGR Toyota. © Michael L. Levitt ©2011 Michael L. Levitt 2011 
Busch was able to rebound from this spin to finish eight in the 53 rd running of the Great American Race. ©,Tami Kelly Pope, LAT Photographic Tami Kelly Pope 2012 
Busch drove this No. 18 M&M’s paint scheme to a 17 th -place finish in 2012. Brian Czobat / autostock © 271 Fryling Ave SW Concord, NC 28025 W 704.786.2919 C 704.904.2745 autostock/Brian Czobat 2013 
A win in the second qualifying race landed him fourth on the grid to start the race, but engine trouble on Lap 151 resulted in a 34 th -place finish. Nigel Kinrade/LAT Photo USA Nigel Kinrade 2014 
Busch battled to a 19 th -place finish after starting 37 th in 2014. © , Michael L. Levitt © 2014, Michael L. Levitt 2015 
Busch was supposed to run this No. 18 green machine in the 57 th annual Daytona 500, but a broken leg following to a hard impact with the inside wall in the XFINITY race sidelined him for the first eight races of the season. He came back to win his first Cup championship. Jasen Vinlove Jasen Vinlove-USA TODAY Sports 
The 2015 champion had the best view in the house of the epic photo finish between JGR teammate Denny Hamlin and Martin Truex Jr., finishing third. NASCAR NASCAR via Getty Images
